# Project AI Assistant Notes

This is a JUCE audio plugin project built with CMake (no Projucer).

## Layout

- `Source/PluginProcessor.{h,cpp}` — the `juce::AudioProcessor` (DSP, state).
- `Source/PluginEditor.{h,cpp}` — the `juce::AudioProcessorEditor` (GUI).
- `CMakeLists.txt` — build configuration; edit the **USER OPTIONS** block at the top for copy settings, and add new `.cpp` files to `PLUGIN_SOURCES`.
- `CMakeUserPresets.json` — per-platform CMake presets.

## Build

JUCE is located via the `JUCE_DIR` environment variable (or a standard install
path). Configure and build with the preset for your platform, for example
`cmake --preset default-macos-arm64 && cmake --build --preset default-macos-arm64`.
See `README.md` for the full per-platform instructions.

## Conventions

- Target the C++ standard set in `CMakeLists.txt` (`CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD`).
- Keep the plugin classes named `PluginProcessor` / `PluginEditor`.
- Refer to the JUCE 8 API: https://docs.juce.com
